description: House and Senate Republicans have voted to approve competing budget measures to pass portions of President Donald Trump’s agenda. Now comes the hard part.
title: House and Senate GOP approved competing budget plans. Now comes the hard part.

description: A $19 strawberry has caused a stir online. And of course, it's sold at Erewhon.
title: A $19 strawberry has caused a stir online. And of course, it's sold at Erewhon.

description: Rarely has a single company's earnings report been so closely watched by Wall Street as a make-or-break moment for the broader market.
title: Aftering waiting with bated breath, Wall Street absorbs Nvidia's latest earnings

description: The Trump administration said in a court filing Wednesday it cannot comply with a federal judge's order to release foreign aid funding by midnight, despite being directed to do so almost two weeks ago.
title: Justice Department tells judges it can't comply with court-ordered deadline to release frozen aid funding

description: California Gov. Gavin Newsom has directed the state's parole board to investigate whether Erik and Lyle Menendez pose an "unreasonable" public safety risk if released from prison, where the siblings have spent decades for the 1989 shotgun murders of their parents, the governor said in a teaser Wednesday for his new podcast.
title: Gov. Gavin Newsom tells parole board to investigate Menendez brothers for clemency

description: President Donald Trump posted a bizarre AI-generated video to social media Monday evening depicting an imagined future version of Gaza with bearded belly dancers on the beach, a giant golden statue of Trump, money raining from the sky, Elon Musk eating pita and a “Trump Gaza” hotel.
title: 'Trump Gaza' video shared by president originated from pro-Israel accounts that have embraced AI

description: For director Brady Corbet, bringing "The Brutalist" to life was a family affair. He and his life partner, Mona Fastvold, who co-wrote the screenplay, are both up for Oscars.
title: For director Brady Corbet, bringing 'The Brutalist' to life was a family affair

description: Several of President Donald Trump’s nominees for senior Justice Department positions faced questions from Senate Democrats on Wednesday about whether it would ever be lawful for a president to defy a court order, with the nominees largely suggesting they couldn't fully answer without more specifics.
title: Democratic senators press Trump nominees on whether officials can ever ignore judges' orders

description: The University of North Texas Health Science Center's failure to obtain permission before using corpses for research may have violated state law, authorities said.
title: Texas probes medical school's use of bodies without consent following NBC News investigation

description: Workplace communications platform Slack experienced an outage Wednesday morning as thousands of users reported they were unable to use the service.
title: Slack platform down as users report service outage

description: Tulsi Gabbard said she fired more than 100 intel officers for using a government chat tool to discuss topics including polyamory, gender transition, and their political views.
title: Tulsi Gabbard fires more than 100 intelligence officers over messages in a chat tool

description: Take a quick look at the Department of Government Efficiency’s list of canceled contracts and you’d think the Agriculture Department spent $25 million on diversity trainings four separate times, while the Consumer Financial Protection Bureau spent $600 million on management consultants.
title: Dozens of DOGE 'receipts' saved no money and killed contracts meant to boost efficiency

description: A Nebraska father struggling to get a Social Security number and valid birth certificate for his toddler with the computer-generated name Unakite Thirteen Hotel gets a reprieve.
title: Girl listed in state records as 'Unakite Thirteen Hotel' finally gets a Social Security number

description: The director of public health in Lubbock, Texas, confirmed that one child has died of measles, the first death related to the disease in the U.S. in a decade. NBC News’ Sam Brock reports on how the medical community is reacting to the rise of a disease that was considered eliminated in the U.S. in 2000.
title: One death confirmed in Texas measles outbreak

description: Michelle Trachtenberg, child actor in "Harriet the Spy" who went on to TV roles in "Buffy the Vampire Slayer" and "Gossip Girl" was found dead at her New York City home, police said Wednesday.
title: Michelle Trachtenberg, 'Buffy the Vampire Slayer' and 'Gossip Girl' star, dies at 39

description: Trump convened his Cabinet secretaries for the first meeting of his new term, gathering agency leaders -- as well as Elon Musk -- who are working to implement his agenda at a spitfire pace.
title: Trump and Elon Musk dominate his first Cabinet meeting

description: Lawyers for plaintiffs said many immigrants are afraid to attend religious services while the government enforces the new rule.
title: Judge blocks Trump immigration policy allowing arrests in churches for some religious groups

description: Dozens of mostly Asian migrants were put on a deportation flight on Thursday. But instead of landing near their home countries, the plane arrived in San José, Costa Rica.
title: In deporting Asians to Central America, Trump strong-arms weaker nations, experts say

description: A woman suspected to be involved in an attempted arson and repeated vandalization of a Northern Colorado Tesla dealership was arrested on Monday—the fourth such incident reported at the location in recent weeks.
title: Woman arrested following fourth vandalism incident at Colorado Tesla dealership

description: Trump administration tells federal agencies to make plans for large-scale layoffs of workers
title: Trump admin tells federal agencies to make plans for large-scale layoffs of workers

description: A Maryland judge on Wednesday sentenced “Real Housewives of Potomac” star Karen Huger to a year behind bars, 11 months after she got drunk and crashed her Maserati into a street sign.
title: 'Real Housewives of Potomac's' Karen Huger sentenced to a year in jail for DUI

description: Trump proposes creating a type of green card program for wealthy foreign investors that would give them permanent residency and a pathway to citizenship for $5 milllion.
title: Trump wants to use $5 million ‘gold cards’ to replace foreign investor visas

description: Washington Post owner Jeff Bezos said Wednesday that the paper’s opinion editor has “decided to step away” as the section takes a new direction focusing on “personal liberties and free markets.”
title: Jeff Bezos overhauls Washington Post opinion section, says it will focus on 'personal liberties and free markets'

description: Everyone who is in the U.S. illegally must register, give fingerprints and provide an address, the Department of Homeland Security said in a statement.
title: Trump administration creates registry for immigrants who are in the US illegally

description: A robotic moon lander known as Athena is scheduled to launch atop a SpaceX Falcon 9 rocket from NASA’s Kennedy Space Center with a mission to explore the moon’s south pole. The same rocket will also launch a moon-mapping satellite developed by NASA, known as the Lunar Trailblazer.
title: New lunar lander set to launch to the Moon’s south pole

description: Alex Ovechkin reached 30 goals in a season for the 19th time in his 20-year NHL career, adding to the league record he set last season with his 18th.
title: Alex Ovechkin sets another goal-scoring record on the march to breaking Wayne Gretzky's tally

description: Watch live coverage as President Trump convenes the first cabinet meeting of his new administration, with Elon Musk expected to be in attendance.
title: Trump holds first cabinet meeting

description: Adnan Syed's murder conviction will remain in place after Baltimore City prosecutors withdrew a motion to vacate the conviction Tuesday.
title: Adnan Syed's murder conviction will stand as he seeks sentence reduction in new hearing

description: Christie's, known for selling fine art, luxury goods, and antiques — opened “Augmented Intelligence” on Feb. 20. The sale of AI art has raked in hundreds of thousands of dollars in bids.
title: Christie's AI art auction draws big-money bids — and thousands of protests signatures

description: West Texas is trying to get a handle on a surging measles crisis that is now up to 124 cases. Health officials say of those confirmed cases, the vast majority were not vaccinated. New Mexico, New Jersey and Georgia have also reported outbreaks. NBC’s Sam Brock reports for TODAY.
title: Measles outbreak in Texas hits 124 cases and continues to climb

description: The Trump administration's Department of Government Efficiency, led by Musk, is coming under increasing scrutiny, including by congressional Republicans.
title: Trump holds first Cabinet meeting, with Elon Musk in attendance

description: Budget fight over limits on Trump's power. Measles vaccine falsely blamed for Texas outbreak. Russia's rare minerals offer. And the Detroit Piston's hot streak.
title: Texas measles outbreak grows and the Detroit Pistons' turnaround: Morning Rundown

description: Many of this year's Academy Award best picture nominees are available to stream. Here's how to watch ahead of the 2025 Oscars this Sunday.
title: Here's where to stream the Oscar best picture contenders

description: The Detroit Pistons spent last season as indisputably the NBA’s worst team. Now, they’re authoring one of its most surprising turnarounds.
title: The Pistons have long been among the NBA's worst teams. Now it's the hottest.

description: A coterie of Trump loyalists is in the early phase of a campaign to rewrite the Constitution so that he can serve another term.
title: Trump keeps toying with a third term — even though the Constitution forbids it

description: President Donald Trump and his billionaire adviser Elon Musk are taking a hatchet to federal agencies, using executive power to impose spending and job cuts that have sparked a polarizing debate in the nation’s capital and across the country.
title: Trump and Musk's slash-and-burn tactics are a sticking point in talks to prevent a shutdown

description: Marlean Ames sued Ohio officials claiming that she was treated unfairly at work because she is straight.
title: Supreme Court weighs straight woman's reverse discrimination claim

description: Playing against his former team for the first time, Los Angeles Lakers guard Luka Dončić recorded a triple double in a 107-99  win against the Dallas Mavericks on Tuesday.
title: Luka Dončić records triple double in first game against Dallas Mavericks

description: Speaker Mike Johnson on Tuesday muscled a multitrillion-dollar budget blueprint through the House by the narrowest of margins — a crucial step for Republicans as they embark on advancing President Donald Trump’s legislative agenda.
title: House narrowly adopts budget plan to advance Trump's agenda in a win for Speaker Johnson

description: House Republicans are becoming wary of in-person town hall meetings after some lawmakers have faced hometown crowds angry about the Trump administration’s cuts.
title: House Republicans hit the brakes on town halls after blowback over Trump's cuts

description: A California boat captain has captured rare video of a super pod of more than 2,000 dolphins breaching off the coast of Monterey Bay, including the more elusive northern right whale dolphin.
title: Rare video captures super pod of 2,000 dolphins breaching and playing off California

description: The California firefighter killed in a stabbing last week was captured on a home security camera bloodied and appearing to plead for her life with the woman now wanted in connection with her death, court records show.
title: Stabbed fire captain seen bloody, pleading for her life, before her wife fled to Mexico, authorities say

description: A lawsuit claims a SWAT team stormed into the wrong Denver apartment while looking for a suspect, traumatizing children despite knowing the man they were looking for lived in another unit.
title: SWAT team raided the wrong Denver apartment and traumatized two young girls, lawsuit says

description: A L.A.-based influencer turned herself in to authorities on Monday after a warrant for her arrest was issued in connection to a car accident that killed a 44-year-old man last year.
title: Los Angeles-based influencer arrested in connection with fatal car crash

description: After a passenger unexpectedly died on a flight from Australia, their body remained seated next to a couple for hours. The incident occurred during the 15-hour flight from Melbourne to Doha. Qatar Airways extended condolences to the passenger’s family and apologized for any distress caused.
title: Couple says they were forced to sit next to dead body for hours on Qatar flight

description: A near miss, recorded by airport surveillance camera, shows a Southwest Airlines plane on its final landing approach, as a small private jet rolls right into its path. The Southwest plane quickly climbs again - out of harm's way - but not before rattling the nerves of those on board and those who see the footage as part of a recent string of events. NBC News’ Erin McLaughlin talks to passengers and an expert about what’s going on in America’s skies.
title: Close call at Chicago’s Midway International Airport after a string of recent mishaps and disasters

description: Federal workers are criticizing layoffs by Elon Musk’s Department of Government Efficiency. 80 percent of the federal workforce is outside of Washington. Meanwhile, Musk is defending his directive for government workers to list their accomplishments, saying that’s what is required by private companies. NBC News’ Gabe Gutierrez reports.
title: Federal workers in limbo over DOGE cuts
